s://api.github.com/users/brandonroberts/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"parents":[{"sha":"b284696088faa4e65f572eb83708329b6eed3f79","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/commits/b284696088faa4e65f572eb83708329b6eed3f79","html_url":"https://github.com/analogjs/analog/commit/b284696088faa4e65f572eb83708329b6eed3f79"}]},{"sha":"b284696088faa4e65f572eb83708329b6eed3f79","node_id":"C_kwDOHnhHGNoAKGIyODQ2OTYwODhmYWE0ZTY1ZjU3MmViODM3MDgzMjliNmVlZDNmNzk","commit":{"author":{"name":"Brandon Roberts","email":"robertsbt@gmail.com","date":"2026-05-15T15:04:31Z"},"committer":{"name":"Brandon Roberts","email":"robertsbt@gmail.com","date":"2026-05-15T21:07:34Z"},"message":"fix(vite-plugin-angular): support the @Service decorator in the fast compiler\n\nAngular 22 introduces the `@Service` decorator as a lighter-weight\nalternative to `@Injectable`. The fast compiler recognised only the five\nclassic decorators, so a `@Service` class fell through uncompiled — no\n`ɵprov`/`ɵfac` emitted.\n\nWire it through the AOT path:\n  - add `Service` to `ANGULAR_DECORATORS` (it self-registers via `ɵprov`,\n    so it stays out of `COMPILABLE_DECORATORS`, same as `@Injectable`)\n  - emit `ɵprov` via `compileService` / `compileDeclareServiceFromMetadata`,\n    gated on `angularVersionAtLeast(22)` since the compiler API and the\n    decorator only exist on Angular 22+\n  - parse the `autoProvided` and `factory` decorator options in metadata\n  - keep `@Service` on the class in the JIT transform, like `@Injectable` —\n    its runtime decorator self-registers `ɵprov`/`ɵfac` lazily\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>","tree":{"sha":"d0c79dfb38308833aee895352261dd7af4640766","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/git/trees/d0c79dfb38308833aee895352261dd7af4640766"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/git/commits/b284696088faa4e65f572eb83708329b6eed3f79","comment_count":0,"verific